## Method payloads (`<data>` inside `[...]`)

Built in `cbIpcCatalog.ts`; mirror `LocalCBclient.java`.

| Method | `data` format (inside `[...]`) |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| `TELL` | `encode(frames)` |
| `UNTELL` | `encode(frames)` |
| `TELL_MODEL` | `[encode(f1),encode(f2),...]` (list inside brackets) |
| `RETELL` | `[encode(untell),encode(tell)]` |
| `ASK` | `OBJNAMES\|FRAMES\|ASK,encode(query),encode(answerRep),encode(rollbackTime)` |
| `HYPO_ASK` | `encode(frames),format,encode(query),encode(answerRep),encode(rollbackTime)` |
| `ENROLL_ME` | `encode(tool),encode(user@host_arch_os)` |
| `CANCEL_ME` | empty |
| `GET_MODULE_PATH` | empty (`pwd`) |
| `SET_MODULE_CONTEXT` | `encode(quotedModulePath)` (`cd`) |
| `GET_MODULE_CONTEXT` | empty |
| `LPI_CALL` | `encode(call)` |
| `NEXT_MESSAGE` | `empty` or message type atom |
| `NOTIFICATION_REQUEST` | `encode(about),targetClientId` |
| `STOP_SERVER` | password string (often `""`) |
| `REPORT_CLIENTS` | empty |

Module arg (`IpcSyntax.typ` `<modulearg>`): optional `, IPCID` or `empty` — mmkit helpers default to omitting it.

